{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab49b16d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8761a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8761a"},"text":"§ 8761a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Uniform clothing: sale to Naval Sea Cadet Corps","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subject to regulations under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s121"},"text":"section 121 of title 40","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary of the Navy, under regulations prescribed by him, may sell any item of enlisted naval uniform clothing that may be spared, at a price representing its fair value, to the Naval Sea Cadet Corps for the sea cadets and to any Federal or State maritime academy having a department of naval science for the maritime cadets and midshipmen. The cost of transportation and delivery of items sold under this section shall be charged to the Naval Sea Cadet Corps and to such Federal and State maritime academies."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab49b16e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/266/s1/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–266, § 1(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/990"},"text":"79 Stat. 990","children":[],"tail":", § 7541a; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/tV/s513/39"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, title V, § 513(39)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2934"},"text":"94 Stat. 2934","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217/s3/b/32"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217, § 3(b)(32)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","a